==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Decumbiture
<hw>De*cum"bi*ture</hw> <pr>(?; 135)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Confinement to a sick bed, or time of taking to one's bed from
sickness.</def> <rj><au>Boyle.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Astrol.)</fld> <def>Aspect of the heavens at the
time of taking to one's sick bed, by which the prognostics of recovery
or death were made.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Decuple</ent>⟦br⟧
